        <item>
            <title><![CDATA[Hello World!]]></title>
            <link>https://scifracx.org/blog/mdx-blog-post</link>
            <guid>https://scifracx.org/blog/mdx-blog-post</guid>
            <pubDate>Fri, 07 Jan 2022 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[Hello all!]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Hello all!</p>
<p>The official website of SciFracX project is now published using <a href="https://docusaurus.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">Docusaurus</a>!</p>
<p>SciFracX is an orgnization aiming at making fractional order computing and modeling easier than ever with Julia.</p>
<p>Now, there are four packages under SciFracX, <a href="https://github.com/SciFracX/FractionalSystems.jl" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">FractionalSystems.jl</a>, <a href="https://github.com/SciFracX/FractionalDiffEq.jl" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">FractionalDiffEq.jl</a>, <a href="https://github.com/SciFracX/FractionalCalculus.jl" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">FractionalCalculus.jl</a> and <a href="https://github.com/SciFracX/FractionalTransforms.jl" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">FractionalTransforms.jl</a>.</p>
<p>If you are also interested in fractional order computing and modeling, JuliaLang and numerical methods binding math and programming, welcome to join SciFracX!!!!!</p>]]></content:encoded>
